	<p class="cs9B6D6CCD"><span class="cs19DD38F">HOUSE RESOLUTION 20</span></p><p class="csF3974999"><span class="csEF05ACC">			</span></p><p class="csA1114BAF"><span class="csEF05ACC">By Del. Hanshaw (Mr. Speaker), Hornbuckle, Adkins, Akers, Amos, Anders, Anderson, Bell, Bridges, Brooks, Browning, Burkhammer, Butler, Campbell, D. Cannon, J. Cannon, Canterbury, Chiarelli, Clark, Clay, Cooper, Coop-Gonzalez, Criss, Crouse, Dean, Dillon, Dittman, Drennan, Eldridge, Ellington, Fehrenbacher, Ferrell, Flanigan, Fluharty, Foggin, Funkhouser, Garcia, Gearheart, Green, Hall, Hamilton, Hansen, Heckert, Hillenbrand, Hite, Holstein, Hornby, Horst, Hott, G. Howell, T. Howell, Jeffries, Jennings, Jordan, Kimble, Kump, Kyle, Leavitt, Lewis, Linville, Lucas, Mallow, Marple, Martin, Masters, Maynor, Mazzocchi, McCormick, McGeehan, Miller, Moore, Parsons, Petitto, Phillips, Pinson, Pritt, Pushkin, Ridenour, Riley, Rohrbach, Roop, Shamblin, Sheedy, B. Smith, D. Smith, Statler, Stephens, Street, Toney, Vance, B Ward, G. Ward, Watt, White, Williams, Willis, Worrell, Young and Zatezalo.</span></p><p class="cs5AA56F76"><span class="csEF05ACC">&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;[Introduced March 2, 2026]</span></p><p class="cs5E6E1156"><span class="cs36FC530">Memorializing the life of the Honorable Larry D. Kump, dedicated public servant, principled legislator, and devoted family man.</span></p><p class="cs5E6E1156"><span class="cs36FC530">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs5E6E1156"><span class="cs36FC530">WHEREAS, The House of Delegates of the West Virginia Legislature extends its profound sorrow on the passing of our esteemed colleague, the Honorable Larry D. Kump, on February 28, 2026; and</span></p><p class="cs5E6E1156"><span class="cs36FC530">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs5E6E1156"><span class="cs36FC530">WHEREAS, Born on January 27, 1948, in Chambersburg, Pennsylvania, Larry Kump dedicated his life to the principles of integrity and honesty in public policy; and</span></p><p class="cs5E6E1156"><span class="cs36FC530">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs5E6E1156"><span class="cs36FC530">WHEREAS, Larry Kump was a proud graduate of Frostburg State University and </span></p><p class="cs5E6E1156"><span class="cs36FC530">Hagerstown Community College, building a distinguished career as a&nbsp;<a class="cs152139EE" href="https://home.wvlegislature.gov/delegate/larry-d-kump/" target="_blank"><span class="csEF05ACC">criminal justice professional</span></a></span><span class="cs36FC530"> and mediator, before entering the legislative arena; and</span></p><p class="cs5E6E1156"><span class="cs36FC530">WHEREAS, Larry Kump served the citizens of Berkeley County with distinction across three separate decades, representing the 52nd, 59th, and 94th Districts during the periods of 2010&ndash;2014, 2018&ndash;2020, and from 2022 until his passing; and</span></p><p class="cs5E6E1156"><span class="cs36FC530">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs5E6E1156"><span class="cs36FC530">WHEREAS, Throughout his tenure, Delegate Kump was known for his&nbsp;</span><span class="csEF05ACC">independent streak</span><span class="cs36FC530"> and his commitment to limited government and individual liberty; and</span></p><p class="cs5E6E1156"><span class="cs36FC530">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs5E6E1156"><span class="cs36FC530">WHEREAS, Beyond his legislative duties, Larry Kump was a devoted husband to his wife, Cheryl, and a father to 13 children, leaving behind a legacy of family devotion and community service as a High Priest in The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-Day Saints; and</span></p><p class="cs5E6E1156"><span class="cs36FC530">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs5E6E1156"><span class="cs36FC530">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs5E6E1156"><span class="cs36FC530">WHEREAS, His presence on the House floor, marked by his&nbsp;mastery of catchphrases such as &ldquo;Great Googly Moogly&rdquo; and &ldquo;For sure and for certain&rdquo;, as well as his tireless advocacy for his constituents, will be deeply missed by all who had the privilege of serving alongside him; therefore, be it</span></p><p class="cs5E6E1156"><span class="cs36FC530">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs5E6E1156"><span class="cs1FB4BF97">Resolved by the House of Delegates:</span></p><p class="cs5E6E1156"><span class="cs36FC530">That the House of Delegates of the West Virginia Legislature hereby expresses its deepest sympathy and condolences to the family of the Honorable Larry D. Kump upon his passing; and, be it</span></p><p class="cs5E6E1156"><span class="cs36FC530">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs5E6E1156"><span class="cs1FB4BF97">Further Resolved,</span><span class="cs36FC530">&nbsp;That the House of Delegates honors the life and legacy of service of the Honorable Larry D. Kump and recognizes his significant contributions to Berkeley County and the State of West Virginia; and, be it</span></p><p class="cs5E6E1156"><span class="cs36FC530">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs5E6E1156"><span class="cs1FB4BF97">Further Resolved,</span><span class="cs36FC530">&nbsp;That the Clerk of the House of Delegates forward a copy of this resolution to the family of the Honorable Larry D. Kump.</span></p><p class="cs96E420EE"><span class="csEF05ACC">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs96E420EE"><span class="cs7B75DFFE">&nbsp;</span></p>


